# Game UI assets — raster only

When creating or replacing **game UI icons, HUD sprites, kill-feed art, shop icons, or any in-game visual asset**:

- Use **real raster images**: PNG (preferred with transparency), WebP, or JPG.
- **Never** use SVG for in-game UI art (no `.svg` in `public/` for HUD/icons).
- Use `GenerateImage` or existing PNG assets; save under `public/` (e.g. `public/ui/`).
- Reference in React with `<img src="...png">`, not inline SVG or `.svg` URLs.

SVG is only acceptable for favicons or external docs — not battle HUD, kill feed, rewards, or shop visuals.
